com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class GetTrustGraphDataRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.GetTrustGraphDataRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class GetTrustGraphDataRequest
extends SiperianRequest
    Retrieves the data to plot the trust decay curve for the specified trust setting. The data is returned as a list of dates and a list of trust values (see TrustGraphData).

    Only custom trust settings are supported. All properties of the trust setting must be specified (see TrustSetting).

    Required Parameter:

    • setTrustSetting(TrustSetting) - Specifies the trust setting for which the trust graph data will be retrieved.

    Usage Example:

    The following example retrieves the trust graph data for a custom trust with maximum trust = 100, minimum trust =0, decay time of 52 weeks, and decay type of "rapid initial, slow later" (see TrustGraphType.RISL):

    GetTrustGraphDataRequest request = new GetTrustGraphDataRequest();
    // All properties of the trust setting are required
    TrustSetting trustSetting =
    TrustSetting.createTrustSettingCustom(100, 0, TrustTimeUnit.WEEK,
    52, TrustGraphType.RISL);
    request.setTrustSetting(trustSetting); // Required
    GetTrustGraphDataResponse response =
    (GetTrustGraphDataResponse) sipClient.process(request);

    See Also:
    GetTrustGraphDataResponse, TrustGraphType, TrustSetting, TrustTimeUnit, SiperianClient.process(SiperianRequest), Serialized Form

    API Pair: GetTrustGraphDataResponse

    API Group: Data Steward
